contextHelp.sensorSnifferRpmThreshold: Disable sensor sniffer above this rpm
contextHelp.launchRpm: A secondary Rev limit engaged by the driver to help launch the vehicle faster
contextHelp.engineSnifferRpmThreshold: Engine sniffer would be disabled above this rpm
contextHelp.multisparkMaxRpm: Disable multispark above this engine speed.
contextHelp.maxAcRpm: Above this RPM, disable AC. Set to 0 to disable check.
contextHelp.maxAcTps: Above this TPS, disable AC. Set to 0 to disable check.
contextHelp.maxAcClt: Above this CLT, disable AC to prevent overheating the engine. Set to 0 to disable check.
contextHelp.multisparkMaxSparkingAngle: This parameter sets the latest that the last multispark can occur after the main ignition event. For example, if the ignition timing is 30 degrees BTDC, and this parameter is set to 45, no multispark will ever be fired after 15 degrees ATDC.
contextHelp.multisparkMaxExtraSparkCount: Configures the maximum number of extra sparks to fire (does not include main spark)
contextHelp.ignitionMode:
Single coil = distributor
Individual coils = one coil per cylinder (COP, coil-near-plug), requires sequential mode
Wasted spark = Fires pairs of cylinders together, either one coil per pair of cylinders or one coil per cylinder
Two distributors = A pair of distributors, found on some BMW, Toyota and other engines
contextHelp.injector_flow:
This is your injector flow at the fuel pressure used in the vehicle. cc/min, cubic centimetre per minute
By the way, g/s = 0.125997881 * (lb/hr)
g/s = 0.125997881 * (cc/min)/10.5
g/s = 0.0119997981 * cc/min
contextHelp.injector_battLagCorr: ms delay between injector open and close dead times
contextHelp.isForcedInduction: Does the vehicle have a turbo or supercharger?
contextHelp.useFordRedundantTps: On some Ford and Toyota vehicles one of the throttle sensors is not linear on the full range, i.e. in the specific range of the positions we effectively have only one sensor.
contextHelp.enableFan1WithAc: Turn on this fan when AC is on.
contextHelp.enableFan2WithAc: Turn on this fan when AC is on.
contextHelp.disableFan1WhenStopped: Inhibit operation of this fan while the engine is not running.
contextHelp.disableFan2WhenStopped: Inhibit operation of this fan while the engine is not running.
contextHelp.enableTrailingSparks: Enable secondary spark outputs that fire after the primary (rotaries, twin plug engines).
contextHelp.etb_use_two_wires: TLE7209 uses two-wire mode. TLE9201 and VNH2SP30 do NOT use two wire mode.
contextHelp.isDoubleSolenoidIdle: Subaru/BMW style where default valve position is somewhere in the middle. First solenoid opens it more while second can close it more than default position.
contextHelp.useSeparateIdleTablesForCrankingTaper: This uses separate ignition timing and VE tables not only for idle conditions, also during the postcranking-to-idle taper transition (See also afterCrankingIACtaperDuration).
contextHelp.useRunningMathForCranking: For cranking either use the specified fixed base fuel mass, or use the normal running math (VE table).
contextHelp.verboseCan: Print incoming and outgoing first bus CAN messages in FOME console
contextHelp.artificialTestMisfire: Experimental setting that will cause a misfire\nDO NOT ENABLE.
contextHelp.useFordRedundantPps: On some Ford and Toyota vehicles one of the pedal sensors is not linear on the full range, i.e. in the specific range of the positions we effectively have only one sensor.
contextHelp.tpsErrorDetectionTooLow: TPS error detection: what throttle % is unrealistically low?\nAlso used for accelerator pedal error detection if so equiped.
contextHelp.tpsErrorDetectionTooHigh: TPS error detection: what throttle % is unrealistically high?\nAlso used for accelerator pedal error detection if so equiped.
contextHelp.cranking_baseFuel: Base mass of the per-cylinder fuel injected during cranking. This is then modified by the multipliers for CLT, IAT, TPS ect, to give the final cranking pulse width.\nA reasonable starting point is 60mg per liter per cylinder.\nex: 2 liter 4 cyl = 500cc/cyl, so 30mg cranking fuel.
contextHelp.cranking_rpm: This sets the RPM limit below which the ECU will use cranking fuel and ignition logic, typically this is around 350-450rpm.
contextHelp.etbRevLimitStart: Once engine speed passes this value, start reducing ETB angle.
contextHelp.etbRevLimitRange: This far above 'Soft limiter start', fully close the throttle. At the bottom of the range, throttle control is normal. At the top of the range, the throttle is fully closed.
contextHelp.map_samplingAngle: MAP averaging sampling start crank degree angle
contextHelp.map_samplingWindow: MAP averaging angle crank degree duration
contextHelp.clt_bias_resistor: Pull-up resistor value on your board
contextHelp.iat_bias_resistor: Pull-up resistor value on your board
contextHelp.knockBandCustom: We calculate knock band based of cylinderBore\n Use this to override - kHz knock band override\nRequires power cycling to effect
contextHelp.cylindersCount: Number of cylinder the engine has.
contextHelp.fuelAlgorithm:
This setting controls which fuel quantity control algorithm is used.
Alpha-N means drive by TPS commonly only used for NA engines
Speed Density requires MAP sensor and is the default choice for may installs
MAF air charge is a cylinder filling based method that uses a mass air flow sensor.
contextHelp.crankingInjectionMode: This is the injection strategy during engine start. See Fuel/Injection settings for more detail. It is suggested to use Simultaneous.
contextHelp.injectionMode: This is where the fuel injection type is defined: Simultaneous means all injectors will fire together at once. Sequential fires the injectors on a per cylinder basis, which requires individually wired injectors. Batched will fire the injectors in groups. If your injectors are individually wired you will also need to enable Two wire batch emulation.
contextHelp.boostControlMinRpm: Minimum RPM to enable boost control. Use this to avoid solenoid noise at idle, and help spool in some cases.
contextHelp.boostControlMinTps: Minimum TPS to enable boost control. Use this to avoid solenoid noise at idle, and help spool in some cases.
contextHelp.boostControlMinMap: Minimum MAP to enable boost control. Use this to avoid solenoid noise at idle, and help spool in some cases.
contextHelp.timingMode: Dynamic uses the timing map to decide the ignition timing, Static timing fixes the timing to the value set below (only use for checking static timing with a timing light).
contextHelp.benchTestCount: How many test bench pulses do you want
contextHelp.crankingTimingAngle: Ignition advance angle used during engine cranking, 5-10 degrees will work as a base setting for most engines.\nThere is tapering towards running timing advance
contextHelp.gapTrackingLengthOverride: How many consecutive gap rations have to match expected ranges for sync to happen
contextHelp.maxIdleVss: Above this speed, disable closed loop idle control. Set to 0 to disable (allow closed loop idle at any speed).
contextHelp.minOilPressureAfterStart: Expected oil pressure after starting the engine. If oil pressure does not reach this level within 5 seconds of engine start, fuel will be cut. Set to 0 to disable and always allow starting.
contextHelp.fixedModeTiming: This value is the ignition timing used when in 'fixed timing' mode, i.e. constant timing\nThis mode is useful when adjusting distributor location.
contextHelp.globalTriggerAngleOffset: Angle between Top Dead Center (TDC) and the first trigger event.\nPositive value in case of synchnization point before TDC and negative in case of synchnization point after TDC\n.Knowing this angle allows us to control timing and other angles in reference to TDC.
contextHelp.analogInputDividerCoefficient: Ratio/coefficient of input voltage dividers on your PCB. For example, use '2' if your board divides 5v into 2.5v. Use '1.66' if your board divides 5v into 3v.
contextHelp.vbattDividerCoeff: This is the ratio of the resistors for the battery voltage, measure the voltage at the battery and then adjust this number until the gauge matches the reading.
contextHelp.fanOnTemperature: Cooling fan turn-on temperature threshold, in Celsius
contextHelp.fanOffTemperature: Cooling fan turn-off temperature threshold, in Celsius
contextHelp.driveWheelRevPerKm: Number of revolutions per kilometer for the wheels your vehicle speed sensor is connected to. Use an online calculator to determine this based on your tire size.
contextHelp.vbattAdcChannel: This is the processor input pin that the battery voltage circuit is connected to, if you are unsure of what pin to use, check the schematic that corresponds to your PCB.
contextHelp.fuelLevelSensor: This is the processor pin that your fuel level sensor in connected to. This is a non standard input so will need to be user defined.
contextHelp.boostControlSafeDutyCycle: Duty cycle to use in case of a sensor failure. This duty cycle should produce the minimum possible amount of boost. This duty is also used in case any of the minimum RPM/TPS/MAP conditions are not met.
contextHelp.camInputs1: Camshaft input could be used either just for engine phase detection if your trigger shape does not include cam sensor as 'primary' channel, or it could be used for Variable Valve timing on one of the camshafts. 1
contextHelp.camInputs2: Camshaft input could be used either just for engine phase detection if your trigger shape does not include cam sensor as 'primary' channel, or it could be used for Variable Valve timing on one of the camshafts. 2
contextHelp.camInputs3: Camshaft input could be used either just for engine phase detection if your trigger shape does not include cam sensor as 'primary' channel, or it could be used for Variable Valve timing on one of the camshafts. 3
contextHelp.camInputs4: Camshaft input could be used either just for engine phase detection if your trigger shape does not include cam sensor as 'primary' channel, or it could be used for Variable Valve timing on one of the camshafts. 4
contextHelp.throttlePedalUpPin: Throttle Pedal not pressed switch - used on some older vehicles like early Mazda Miata
contextHelp.manIdlePosition: Value between 0 and 100 used in Manual mode
contextHelp.knockRetardAggression: Ignition timing to remove when a knock event occurs.
contextHelp.knockRetardReapplyRate: After a knock event, reapply timing at this rate.
contextHelp.engineSyncCam: Select which cam is used for engine sync. Other cams will be used only for VVT measurement, but not engine sync.
contextHelp.vssFilterReciprocal: Set this so your vehicle speed signal is responsive, but not noisy. Larger value give smoother but slower response.
contextHelp.vssGearRatio: Number of turns of your vehicle speed sensor per turn of the wheels. For example if your sensor is on the transmission output, enter your axle/differential ratio. If you are using a hub-mounted sensor, enter a value of 1.0.
contextHelp.vssToothCount: Number of pulses output per revolution of the shaft where your VSS is mounted. For example, GM applications of the T56 output 17 pulses per revolution of the transmission output shaft.
contextHelp.idleVeOverrideMode: Override the Y axis (load) value used for only the Idle VE table.\nAdvanced users only: If you aren't sure you need this, you probably don't need this.
contextHelp.o2heaterPin: On-off O2 sensor heater control. 'ON' if engine is running, 'OFF' if stopped or cranking.
contextHelp.malfunctionIndicatorPin: Check engine light, also malfunction indicator light. Always blinks once on boot.
contextHelp.clutchDownPin: Some cars have a switch to indicate that clutch pedal is all the way down
contextHelp.mc33_t_min_boost: Minimum allowed time for the boost phase. If the boost target current is reached before this time elapses, it is assumed that the injector has failed short circuit.
contextHelp.acIdleExtraOffset: Additional idle % while A/C is active
contextHelp.finalGearRatio: Ratio between the wheels and your transmission output.
contextHelp.wastegatePositionMin: Voltage when the wastegate is closed.\nYou probably don't have one of these!
contextHelp.wastegatePositionMax: Voltage when the wastegate is fully open.\nYou probably don't have one of these!\n1 volt = 1000 units
contextHelp.secondSolenoidPin: Some Subaru and some Mazda use double-solenoid idle air valve
contextHelp.compressionRatio: Just for reference really, not taken into account by any logic at this point
contextHelp.triggerSimulatorPins1: Generate a synthetic trigger signal for an external ECU 1
contextHelp.triggerSimulatorPins2: Generate a synthetic trigger signal for an external ECU 2
contextHelp.rusefiVerbose29b: Use 11 bit (standard) or 29 bit (extended) IDs for FOME verbose CAN format.
contextHelp.useStepperIdle: This setting should only be used if you have a stepper motor idle valve and a stepper motor driver installed.
contextHelp.enableVerboseCanTx: CAN broadcast using custom FOME protocol\nenable can_broadcast/disable can_broadcast
contextHelp.isFasterEngineSpinUpEnabled: If enabled, try to fire the engine before a full engine cycle has been completed using RPM estimated from the last 90 degrees of engine rotation. As soon as the trigger syncs plus 90 degrees rotation, fuel and ignition events will occur. If disabled, worst case may require up to 4 full crank rotations before any events are scheduled.
contextHelp.coastingFuelCutEnabled: This setting disables fuel injection while the engine is in overrun, this is useful as a fuel saving measure and to prevent back firing.
contextHelp.useIacTableForCoasting: Override the IAC position during overrun conditions to help reduce engine breaking, this can be helpful for large engines in light weight cars or engines that have trouble returning to idle.
contextHelp.disableEtbWhenEngineStopped: Allows disabling the ETB when the engine is stopped. You may not like the power draw or PWM noise from the motor, so this lets you turn it off until it's necessary.
contextHelp.pauseEtbControl: Disable the electronic throttle motor and DC idle motor for testing.\nThis mode is for testing ETB/DC idle position sensors, etc without actually driving the throttle.
contextHelp.minimumBoostClosedLoopMap: Minimum MAP before closed loop boost is enabled. Use to prevent misbehavior upon entering boost.
contextHelp.acFanPin: Optional Radiator Fan used with A/C
contextHelp.idlePidRpmUpperLimit: How far above idle speed do we consider idling?\nFor example, if target = 800, this param = 200, then anything below 1000 RPM is considered idle.
contextHelp.applyNonlinearBelowPulse: Apply nonlinearity correction below a pulse of this duration. Pulses longer than this duration will receive no adjustment.
contextHelp.clutchUpPin: Some vehicles have a switch to indicate that clutch pedal is all the way up
contextHelp.stoichRatioSecondary: Stoichiometric ratio for your secondary fuel. This value is used when the Flex Fuel sensor indicates E100, typically 9.0
contextHelp.etbMaximumPosition: Maximum allowed ETB position. Some throttles go past fully open, so this allows you to limit it to fully open.
contextHelp.sdCardLogFrequency: Rate the ECU will log to the SD card, in hz (log lines per second).
contextHelp.starterRelayDisablePinMode: On some vehicles we can disable starter once engine is already running
contextHelp.mapMinBufferLength: This many MAP samples are used to estimate the current MAP. This many samples are considered, and the minimum taken. Recommended value is 1 for single-throttle engines, and your number of cylinders for individual throttle bodies.
contextHelp.idlePidDeactivationTpsThreshold: Below this throttle position, the engine is considered idling. If you have an electronic throttle, this checks accelerator pedal position instead of throttle position, and should be set to 1-2%.
contextHelp.startCrankingDuration: Maximum time to crank starter when start/stop button is pressed
contextHelp.lambdaProtectionTimeout: Only respond once lambda is out of range for this period of time. Use to avoid transients triggering lambda protection when not needed
contextHelp.useHbridgesToDriveIdleStepper: If enabled we use two H-bridges to drive stepper idle air valve
contextHelp.enableCanVss: Read VSS from OEM CAN bus according to selected CAN vehicle configuration.
contextHelp.stftIgnoreErrorMagnitude: If enabled, adjust at a constant rate instead of a rate proportional to the current lambda error. This mode may be easier to tune, and more tolerant of sensor noise.
contextHelp.verboseVVTDecoding: Verbose info in console below engineSnifferRpmThreshold\nenable vvt_details
contextHelp.alphaNUseIat: In Alpha-N mode, compensate for air temperature.
contextHelp.useRawOutputToDriveIdleStepper: If enabled we use four Push-Pull outputs to directly drive stepper idle air valve coilss
contextHelp.verboseCan2: Print incoming and outgoing second bus CAN messages in FOME console
contextHelp.etbIo1_controlPin: Acts as EN pin in two-wire mode
contextHelp.etbIo2_controlPin: Acts as EN pin in two-wire mode
contextHelp.launchTimingRpmRange: Range from Launch RPM for Timing Retard to activate
contextHelp.launchBoostDuty: Duty Cycle for the Boost Solenoid
contextHelp.hardCutRpmRange: Range from Launch RPM to activate Hard Cut
contextHelp.stft_maxIdleRegionRpm: Below this RPM, the idle region is active
contextHelp.stft_maxOverrunLoad: Below this engine load, the overrun region is active
contextHelp.stft_minPowerLoad: Above this engine load, the power region is active
contextHelp.stft_deadband: When close to correct AFR, pause correction. This can improve stability by not changing the adjustment if the error is extremely small, but is not required.
contextHelp.stft_minClt: Below this temperature, correction is disabled.
contextHelp.stft_minAfr: Below this AFR, correction is paused
contextHelp.stft_maxAfr: Above this AFR, correction is paused
contextHelp.stft_startupDelay: Delay after starting the engine before beginning closed loop correction.
contextHelp.stft_cellCfgs1_timeConstant: Time constant for correction while in this cell: this sets responsiveness of the closed loop correction. A value of 5.0 means it will try to make most of the correction within 5 seconds, and a value of 1.0 will try to correct within 1 second.
contextHelp.stft_cellCfgs2_timeConstant: Time constant for correction while in this cell: this sets responsiveness of the closed loop correction. A value of 5.0 means it will try to make most of the correction within 5 seconds, and a value of 1.0 will try to correct within 1 second.
contextHelp.stft_cellCfgs3_timeConstant: Time constant for correction while in this cell: this sets responsiveness of the closed loop correction. A value of 5.0 means it will try to make most of the correction within 5 seconds, and a value of 1.0 will try to correct within 1 second.
contextHelp.stft_cellCfgs4_timeConstant: Time constant for correction while in this cell: this sets responsiveness of the closed loop correction. A value of 5.0 means it will try to make most of the correction within 5 seconds, and a value of 1.0 will try to correct within 1 second.
contextHelp.stepperDcIo1_controlPin: Acts as EN pin in two-wire mode
contextHelp.stepperDcIo2_controlPin: Acts as EN pin in two-wire mode
contextHelp.engineMake: For example, BMW, GM or Chevrolet
contextHelp.vehicleName: For example, Hunchback or Orange Miata\nVehicle name has to be unique between your vehicles.
contextHelp.vvtOffsets1: Angle between cam sensor and VVT zero position 1
contextHelp.vvtOffsets2: Angle between cam sensor and VVT zero position 2
contextHelp.vvtOffsets3: Angle between cam sensor and VVT zero position 3
contextHelp.vvtOffsets4: Angle between cam sensor and VVT zero position 4
contextHelp.widebandOnSecondBus: Select which bus the wideband controller is attached to.
contextHelp.fuelClosedLoopCorrectionEnabled: Enables lambda sensor closed loop feedback for fuelling.
contextHelp.silentTriggerError: Sometimes we have a performance issue while printing error
contextHelp.tachPulseDurationAsDutyCycle: Treat milliseconds value as duty cycle value, i.e. 0.5ms would become 50%
contextHelp.isAlternatorControlEnabled: This enables smart alternator control and activates the extra alternator settings.
contextHelp.invertPrimaryTriggerSignal: Invert the signal from the primary trigger sensor.
contextHelp.invertSecondaryTriggerSignal: Invert the signal from the secondary trigger sensor.
contextHelp.cutSparkOnHardLimit: Be careful enabling this: some engines are known to self-disassemble their valvetrain with a spark cut. Fuel cut is much safer.
contextHelp.launchSparkCutEnable: This is the Cut Mode normally used
contextHelp.skippedWheelOnCam: Where is your primary skipped wheel located?
contextHelp.isCylinderCleanupEnabled: When enabled if TPS is held above 95% no fuel is injected while cranking to clear excess fuel from the cylinders.
contextHelp.complexWallModel: Should we use tables to vary tau/beta based on CLT/MAP, or just with fixed values?
contextHelp.overrideCrankingIacSetting: If enabled, use separate temperature multiplier table for cranking idle position.\nIf disabled, use normal running multiplier table applied to the cranking base position.
contextHelp.useSeparateAdvanceForIdle: This activates a separate ignition timing table for idle conditions, this can help idle stability by using ignition retard and advance either side of the desired idle speed. Extra retard at low idle speeds will prevent stalling and extra advance at high idle speeds can help reduce engine power and slow the idle speed.
contextHelp.useSeparateVeForIdle: This activates a separate fuel table for Idle, this allows fine tuning of the idle fuelling.
contextHelp.verboseTriggerSynchDetails: Verbose info in console below engineSnifferRpmThreshold\nenable trigger_details
contextHelp.isManualSpinningMode: Usually if we have no trigger events that means engine is stopped\nUnless we are troubleshooting and spinning the engine by hand - this case a longer\ndelay is needed
contextHelp.useSeparateAdvanceForCranking: In Constant mode, timing is automatically tapered to running as RPM increases.\nIn Table mode, the Cranking ignition advance table is used directly.
contextHelp.useAdvanceCorrectionsForCranking: This enables the various ignition corrections during cranking (IAT, CLT, FSIO and PID idle).\nYou probably don't need this.
contextHelp.flexCranking: Enable a second cranking table to use for E100 flex fuel, interpolating between the two based on flex fuel sensor.
contextHelp.useIacPidMultTable: This flag allows to use a special 'PID Multiplier' table (0.0-1.0) to compensate for nonlinear nature of IAC-RPM controller
contextHelp.launchSmoothRetard: Interpolates the Ignition Retard from 0 to 100% within the RPM Range
contextHelp.isPhaseSyncRequiredForIgnition: Some engines are OK running semi-random sequential while other engine require phase synchronization
contextHelp.useCltBasedRpmLimit: If enabled, use a curve for RPM limit (based on coolant temperature) instead of a constant value.
contextHelp.forceO2Heating: If enabled, don't wait for engine start to heat O2 sensors. WARNING: this will reduce the life of your sensor, as condensation in the exhaust from a cold start can crack the sensing element.
contextHelp.invertVvtControlIntake: If increased VVT duty cycle increases the indicated VVT angle, set this to 'advance'. If it decreases, set this to 'retard'. Most intake cams use 'advance', and most exhaust cams use 'retard'.
contextHelp.invertVvtControlExhaust: If increased VVT duty cycle increases the indicated VVT angle, set this to 'advance'. If it decreases, set this to 'retard'. Most intake cams use 'advance', and most exhaust cams use 'retard'.
contextHelp.sdTriggerLog: 'Trigger' mode will write a high speed log of trigger events (warning: uses lots of space!). 'Normal' mode will write a standard MLG of sensors, engine function, etc. similar to the one captured in TunerStudio.
contextHelp.acIdleRpmBump: Extra idle target speed when A/C is enabled. Some cars need the extra speed to keep the AC efficient while idling.
contextHelp.mapAveragingSchedulingAtIndex: At what trigger index should some MAP-related math be executed? This is a performance trick to reduce load on synchronization trigger callback.
contextHelp.tachPulseDuractionMs: Duration in ms or duty cycle depending on selected mode
contextHelp.wwaeTau: Length of time the deposited wall fuel takes to dissipate after the start of acceleration.
contextHelp.airTaperRpmRange: RPM range above upper limit for extra air taper
contextHelp.mapErrorDetectionTooLow: kPa value which is too low to be true
contextHelp.mapErrorDetectionTooHigh: kPa value which is too high to be true
contextHelp.multisparkSparkDuration: How long to wait for the spark to fire before recharging the coil for another spark.
contextHelp.multisparkDwell: This sets the dwell time for subsequent sparks. The main spark's dwell is set by the dwell table.
contextHelp.wwaeBeta: 0 = No fuel settling on port walls 1 = All the fuel settling on port walls setting this to 0 disables the wall wetting enrichment.
contextHelp.startUpFuelPumpDuration: on IGN voltage detection turn fuel pump on to build fuel pressure
contextHelp.idlePidRpmDeadZone: If the RPM closer to target than this value, disable closed loop idle correction to prevent oscillation
contextHelp.targetVBatt: This is the target battery voltage the alternator PID control will attempt to maintain
contextHelp.afterCrankingIACtaperDuration: This is the duration in cycles that the IAC will take to reach its normal idle position, it can be used to hold the idle higher for a few seconds after cranking to improve startup.
contextHelp.iacByTpsTaper: Extra IAC, in percent between 0 and 100, tapered between zero and idle deactivation TPS value
contextHelp.auxSerialTxPin: Auxiliary sensor serial, not to be confused with secondary calibration serial
contextHelp.auxSerialRxPin: Auxiliary sensor serial, not to be confused with secondary calibration serial
contextHelp.tpsAccelLookback: How long to look back for TPS-based acceleration enrichment. Increasing this time will trigger enrichment for longer when a throttle position change occurs.
contextHelp.coastingFuelCutVssLow: Below this speed, disable DFCO. Use this to prevent jerkiness from fuel enable/disable in low gears.
contextHelp.coastingFuelCutVssHigh: Above this speed, allow DFCO. Use this to prevent jerkiness from fuel enable/disable in low gears.
contextHelp.noFuelTrimAfterDfcoTime: Pause closed loop fueling after deceleration fuel cut occurs. Set this to a little longer than however long is required for normal fueling behavior to resume after fuel cut.
contextHelp.tpsAccelEnrichmentThreshold: Maximum change delta of TPS percentage over the 'length'. Actual TPS change has to be above this value in order for TPS/TPS acceleration to kick in.
contextHelp.injectionTimingMode: Sets what part of injection's is controlled by the injection phase table.
contextHelp.fan1ExtraIdle: Additional idle % when fan #1 is active
contextHelp.tpsDecelEnleanmentThreshold: For decel we simply multiply delta of TPS and tFor decel we do not use table?!
contextHelp.tpsDecelEnleanmentMultiplier: Magic multiplier, we multiply delta of TPS and get fuel squirt duration
contextHelp.veOverrideMode: Override the Y axis (load) value used for the VE table.\nAdvanced users only: If you aren't sure you need this, you probably don't need this.
contextHelp.afrOverrideMode: Override the Y axis (load) value used for the AFR table.\nAdvanced users only: If you aren't sure you need this, you probably don't need this.
contextHelp.mc33_hpfp_i_hold_off: How long to deactivate power when hold current is reached before applying power again
contextHelp.mc33_hpfp_max_hold: Maximum amount of time the solenoid can be active before assuming a programming error
contextHelp.stepperDcInvertedPins: Enable if DC-motor driver (H-bridge) inverts the signals (eg. RZ7899 on Hellen boards)
contextHelp.injectorFlowAsMassFlow: Select whether to configure injector flow in volumetric flow (defualt, cc/min) or mass flow (g/s).
contextHelp.ignOverrideMode: Override the Y axis (load) value used for the ignition table.\nAdvanced users only: If you aren't sure you need this, you probably don't need this.
contextHelp.injectorPressureType: Select which fuel pressure sensor measures the pressure of the fuel at your injectors.
contextHelp.boostCutPressure: MAP value above which fuel is cut in case of overboost.\nSet to 0 to disable overboost cut.
contextHelp.fixedTiming: Fixed timing, useful for TDC testing
contextHelp.vvtPins1: VVT output solenoid pin for this cam 1
contextHelp.vvtPins2: VVT output solenoid pin for this cam 2
contextHelp.vvtPins3: VVT output solenoid pin for this cam 3
contextHelp.vvtPins4: VVT output solenoid pin for this cam 4
contextHelp.crankingIACposition: This is the IAC position during cranking, some engines start better if given more air during cranking to improve cylinder filling.
contextHelp.minimumIgnitionTiming: Minimim timing advance allowed. No spark on any cylinder will ever fire after this angle BTDC. For example, setting -10 here means no spark ever fires later than 10 deg ATDC. Note that this only concerns the primary spark: any trailing sparks or multispark may violate this constraint.
contextHelp.maximumIgnitionTiming: Maximum timing advance allowed. No spark on any cylinder will ever fire before this angle BTDC. For example, setting 45 here means no spark ever fires earlier than 45 deg BTDC
contextHelp.fan2ExtraIdle: Additional idle % when fan #2 is active
contextHelp.primingDelay: Delay to allow fuel pressure to build before firing the priming pulse.
contextHelp.injectorCompensationMode: None = I have a MAP-referenced fuel pressure regulator\nFixed rail pressure = I have an atmosphere-referenced fuel pressure regulator (returnless, typically)\nSensed rail pressure = I have a fuel pressure sensor
contextHelp.fuelReferencePressure: This is the pressure at which your injector flow is known.\nFor example if your injectors flow 400cc/min at 3.5 bar, enter 350kpa here.
contextHelp.postCrankingFactor: Fuel multiplier (enrichment) immediately after engine start
contextHelp.postCrankingDurationSec: Time over which to taper out after start enrichment
contextHelp.auxTempSensor1_bias_resistor: Pull-up resistor value on your board
contextHelp.auxTempSensor2_bias_resistor: Pull-up resistor value on your board
contextHelp.stepperNumMicroSteps: For micro-stepping, make sure that PWM frequency (etbFreq) is high enough
contextHelp.stepperMinDutyCycle: Use to limit the current when the stepper motor is idle, not moving (100% = no limit)
contextHelp.stepperMaxDutyCycle: Use to limit the max.current through the stepper motor (100% = no limit)
contextHelp.spi1MosiMode: Modes count be used for 3v<>5v integration using pull-ups/pull-downs etc.
contextHelp.fan2OnTemperature: Cooling fan turn-on temperature threshold, in Celsius
contextHelp.fan2OffTemperature: Cooling fan turn-off temperature threshold, in Celsius
contextHelp.etbJamTimeout: Time required to detect a stuck throttle.
contextHelp.etbExpAverageLength: By the way ETB PID runs at 500hz, length in 1/500 of second here.
contextHelp.coastingFuelCutRpmHigh: This sets the RPM above which fuel cut is active.
contextHelp.coastingFuelCutRpmLow: This sets the RPM below which fuel cut is deactivated, this prevents jerking or issues transitioning to idle
contextHelp.coastingFuelCutTps: Throttle position below which fuel cut is active. With an electronic throttle enabled, this checks against pedal position.
contextHelp.coastingFuelCutClt: Fuel cutoff is disabled when the engine is cold.
contextHelp.pidExtraForLowRpm: Increases PID reaction for RPM<target by adding extra percent to PID-error
contextHelp.coastingFuelCutMap: MAP value above which fuel injection is re-enabled.
contextHelp.tChargeAirCoefMin: Heat transfer coefficient at zero flow.\n0 means the air charge is fully heated to the same temperature as CLT.\n1 means the air charge gains no heat, and enters the cylinder at the temperature measured by IAT.
contextHelp.tChargeAirCoefMax: Heat transfer coefficient at high flow, as defined by max air flow.\n0 means the air charge is fully heated to the same temperature as CLT.\n1 means the air charge gains no heat, and enters the cylinder at the temperature measured by IAT.
contextHelp.tChargeAirFlowMax: High flow point for heat transfer estimation.\nSet this to perhaps 50-75% of your maximum airflow at wide open throttle.
contextHelp.tChargeAirIncrLimit: Maximum allowed rate of increase allowed for the estimated charge temperature
contextHelp.tChargeAirDecrLimit: Maximum allowed rate of decrease allowed for the estimated charge temperature
contextHelp.etbRocExpAverageLength: By the way ETB PID runs at 500hz, length in 1/500 of second here.
contextHelp.tpsAccelFractionPeriod: A delay in cycles between fuel-enrich. portions
contextHelp.tpsAccelFractionDivisor: A fraction divisor: 1 or less = entire portion at once, or split into diminishing fractions
contextHelp.stoichRatioPrimary:
Stoichiometric ratio for your primary fuel. When Flex Fuel is enabled, this value is used when the Flex Fuel sensor indicates E0.
E0 = 14.7
E10 = 14.1
E85 = 9.9
E100 = 9.0
contextHelp.etbIdleThrottleRange: This sets the range of the idle control on the ETB. At 100% idle position, the value specified here sets the base ETB position.
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect1: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 1
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect2: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 2
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect3: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 3
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect4: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 4
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect5: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 5
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect6: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 6
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect7: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 7
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect8: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 8
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect9: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 9
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect10: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 10
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect11: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 11
contextHelp.cylinderBankSelect12: Select which fuel correction bank this cylinder belongs to. Group cylinders that share the same O2 sensor 12
contextHelp.gppwm1_pin: Select a pin to use for PWM or on-off output.
contextHelp.gppwm1_dutyIfError: If an error (with a sensor, etc) is detected, this value is used instead of reading from the table.\nThis should be a safe value for whatever hardware is connected to prevent damage.
contextHelp.gppwm1_pwmFrequency: Select a frequency to run PWM at.\nSet this to 0hz to enable on-off mode.
contextHelp.gppwm1_onAboveDuty: Hysteresis: in on-off mode, turn the output on when the table value is above this duty.
contextHelp.gppwm1_offBelowDuty: Hysteresis: in on-off mode, turn the output off when the table value is below this duty.
contextHelp.gppwm1_loadAxis: Selects the Y axis to use for the table.
contextHelp.gppwm1_rpmAxis: Selects the X axis to use for the table.
contextHelp.gppwm2_pin: Select a pin to use for PWM or on-off output.
contextHelp.gppwm2_dutyIfError: If an error (with a sensor, etc) is detected, this value is used instead of reading from the table.\nThis should be a safe value for whatever hardware is connected to prevent damage.
contextHelp.gppwm2_pwmFrequency: Select a frequency to run PWM at.\nSet this to 0hz to enable on-off mode.
contextHelp.gppwm2_onAboveDuty: Hysteresis: in on-off mode, turn the output on when the table value is above this duty.
contextHelp.gppwm2_offBelowDuty: Hysteresis: in on-off mode, turn the output off when the table value is below this duty.
contextHelp.gppwm2_loadAxis: Selects the Y axis to use for the table.
contextHelp.gppwm2_rpmAxis: Selects the X axis to use for the table.
contextHelp.gppwm3_pin: Select a pin to use for PWM or on-off output.
contextHelp.gppwm3_dutyIfError: If an error (with a sensor, etc) is detected, this value is used instead of reading from the table.\nThis should be a safe value for whatever hardware is connected to prevent damage.
contextHelp.gppwm3_pwmFrequency: Select a frequency to run PWM at.\nSet this to 0hz to enable on-off mode.
contextHelp.gppwm3_onAboveDuty: Hysteresis: in on-off mode, turn the output on when the table value is above this duty.
contextHelp.gppwm3_offBelowDuty: Hysteresis: in on-off mode, turn the output off when the table value is below this duty.
contextHelp.gppwm3_loadAxis: Selects the Y axis to use for the table.
contextHelp.gppwm3_rpmAxis: Selects the X axis to use for the table.
contextHelp.gppwm4_pin: Select a pin to use for PWM or on-off output.
contextHelp.gppwm4_dutyIfError: If an error (with a sensor, etc) is detected, this value is used instead of reading from the table.\nThis should be a safe value for whatever hardware is connected to prevent damage.
contextHelp.gppwm4_pwmFrequency: Select a frequency to run PWM at.\nSet this to 0hz to enable on-off mode.
contextHelp.gppwm4_onAboveDuty: Hysteresis: in on-off mode, turn the output on when the table value is above this duty.
contextHelp.gppwm4_offBelowDuty: Hysteresis: in on-off mode, turn the output off when the table value is below this duty.
contextHelp.gppwm4_loadAxis: Selects the Y axis to use for the table.
contextHelp.gppwm4_rpmAxis: Selects the X axis to use for the table.
contextHelp.mc33_t_max_boost: Maximum allowed boost phase time. If the injector current doesn't reach the threshold before this time elapses, it is assumed that the injector is missing or has failed open circuit.
contextHelp.knockBaseNoise: Knock sensor output knock detection threshold depending on current RPM.
contextHelp.maxCamPhaseResolveRpm: Below this RPM, use camshaft information to synchronize the crank's position for full sequential operation. Use this if your cam sensor does weird things at high RPM. Set to 0 to disable, and always use cam to help sync crank.
contextHelp.dfcoDelay: Delay before cutting fuel. Set to 0 to cut immediately with no delay. May cause rumbles and pops out of your exhaust...
contextHelp.acDelay: Delay before engaging the AC compressor. Set to 0 to engage immediately with no delay. Use this to prevent bogging at idle when AC engages.
contextHelp.hpfpPeakPos: Crank angle ATDC of first lobe peak
contextHelp.hpfpMinAngle: If the requested activation time is below this angle, don't bother running the pump
contextHelp.hpfpPumpVolume: Size of the pump chamber in cc. Typical Bosch HDP5 has a 9.0mm diameter, typical BMW N* stroke is 4.4mm.
contextHelp.hpfpActivationAngle: How long to keep the valve activated (in order to allow the pump to build pressure and keep the valve open on its own)
contextHelp.hpfpTargetDecay: The fastest rate the target pressure can be reduced by. This is because HPFP have no way to bleed off pressure other than injecting fuel.
contextHelp.vvtActivationDelayMs: We need to give engine time to build oil pressure without diverting it to VVT
contextHelp.tpsSecondaryMaximum: For Ford TPS, use 53%. For Toyota ETCS-i, use ~65%
contextHelp.rpmHardLimitHyst: If the hard limit is 7200rpm and hysteresis is 200rpm, then when the ECU sees 7200rpm, fuel/ign will cut, and stay cut until 7000rpm (7200-200) is reached
contextHelp.ignTestCount: How many test bench pulses do you want
contextHelp.canVssScaling: Scale the reported vehicle speed value from CAN. Example: Parameter set to 1.1, CAN VSS reports 50kph, ECU will report 55kph instead.
contextHelp.oilTempSensor_bias_resistor: Pull-up resistor value on your board
contextHelp.fuelTempSensor_bias_resistor: Pull-up resistor value on your board
contextHelp.ambientTempSensor_bias_resistor: Pull-up resistor value on your board
contextHelp.compressorDischargeTemperature_bias_resi: Pull-up resistor value on your board
contextHelp.throttleInletPressureChannel: Place the sensor before the throttle, but after any turbocharger/supercharger and intercoolers if fitted. Uses the same calibration as the MAP sensor.
contextHelp.compressorDischargePressureChannel: Place the sensor after the turbocharger/supercharger, but before any intercoolers if fitted. Uses the same calibration as the MAP sensor.
contextHelp.maxInjectorDutyInstant: If injector duty cycle hits this value, instantly cut fuel.
contextHelp.maxInjectorDutySustained: If injector duty cycle hits this value for the specified delay time, cut fuel.
contextHelp.maxInjectorDutySustainedTimeout: Timeout period for duty cycle over the sustained limit to trigger duty cycle protection.
contextHelp.speedometerPulsePerKm: Number of speedometer pulses per kilometer travelled.
contextHelp.etbBiasBins: target TPS value, 0 to 100%\nTODO: use int8 data date once we template interpolation method
contextHelp.sparkDwellRpmBins: On Single Coil or Wasted Spark setups you have to lower dwell at high RPM
contextHelp.cltIdleRpmBins: CLT-based target RPM for automatic idle controller
contextHelp.crankingTpsCoef: Cranking fuel correction coefficient based on TPS
contextHelp.crankingAdvanceBins: Optional timing advance table for Cranking (see useSeparateAdvanceForCranking)
contextHelp.crankingAdvance: Optional timing advance table for Cranking (see useSeparateAdvanceForCranking)
contextHelp.cltCrankingCorrBins: CLT-based cranking position multiplier for simple manual idle controller
contextHelp.cltCrankingCorr: CLT-based cranking position multiplier for simple manual idle controller
contextHelp.idleAdvanceBins: Optional timing advance table for Idle (see useSeparateAdvanceForIdle)
contextHelp.idleAdvance: Optional timing advance table for Idle (see useSeparateAdvanceForIdle)
contextHelp.cltIdleCorrBins: CLT-based idle position multiplier for simple manual idle controller
contextHelp.cltIdleCorr: CLT-based idle position multiplier for simple manual idle controller
contextHelp.mafDecoding: Also known as MAF transfer function.\nkg/hour value.\nBy the way 2.081989116 kg/h = 1 ft3/m
contextHelp.throttleEstimateEffectiveAreaValues: In units of g/s normalized to choked flow conditions
